-- Beach Energy to Invest $46 Million in Tanzania Oil Search, Daily News Says
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-06-24T06:56:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/beach-energy-to-invest-46-million-in-tanzania-oil-search-daily-news-says.html

          
          
             Australiaâ€™s Beach Energy Ltd. agreed
to invest at least $46 million in Tanzania searching for oil and
gas in the unexplored western Lake Tanganyika area, the  Daily
News  said, citing Energy and Minerals Minister  William Ngeleja .  
 The production sharing agreement with the government brings
to 14 the number of oil and gas explorers operating in the East
African nation, Ngeleja said, according to the Dar es Salaam-
based newspaper today.  
 Lake Tanganyika, situated in the Great Rift Valley, also
borders Democratic Republic of Congo, Zambia and Burundi.  
